            <thetext>The use of the @signature tag with parameter names is not well documented.

thron7 answered on the mailing list:

  If you use the @signature tag, use it in this way:
  @signature function(path1, path2, path3)
  @param path1 {String} path1 description
  @param path2 {String} path2 description
  @param path3 {String} path3 description

  You see, you just use the parameter names in the @signature tag, and then
  provide @param tags for each them in the usual way. But you are right,
  this is insufficiently described in the manual, please open a bug for it.
  You can just insert this comment for the description.

I created a pull request to enhance the documentation:
https://github.com/qooxdoo/qooxdoo/pull/8</thetext>
